          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "LCS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Quasimonochromatic gamma-rays produced by means",
                " of laser Compton backscattering (LCS), lambda = 532",
                " nm laser photons were used. The energy spread of the",
                " LCS gamma-ray beam was 0.8 - 1.6 MeV in full width at",
                "half maximum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Ten 1 cm x 1 cm 100 micron-thick Ta and Au foils,",
                " 99.95%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "T",
              "coded_information": [
                "RINGR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Direct neutron counting measurement of total",
                " photoneutron cross section using 20 3He proportional",
                " counters (three concentric rings of 4, 8, and 8",
                " detectors) embedded at 38, 70 and 100 mm,",
                " respectively from the axis in a polyethylene",
                " moderator."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "G",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Photoactivation measurement of partial cross",
                "section for the ground state in 181Ta."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "T",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 3He proportional counters to detect neutron."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "T",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " to measure the intensity of the LCS gamma-rays."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "G",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Hyperpure Germanium detector of planer type",
                " with active volume of 114 cm**3 to measure the energy",
                " distribution of the LCS gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "T",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "G",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "M",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 180Ta is the one and only naturally occurring isomer.",
                "It is present in nature in an isomeric state at",
                "excitation energy of 75.3 keV with the spin-parity 9-.",
                "The isomer has the half-life greater than",
                "1.2 x 10**15 yr, in contrast to the short-lived ground",
                "state (1+; 8.152 h) in 180Ta. Therefore the subtracting",
                "procedure was used: SIG-m = (SIG-tot) - (SIG-gs).     M"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "T",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainty is 4.4% (3% for",
                " initial photon flux and 3.2% for neutron detection",
                " efficiency)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "G",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainty for the ground",
                " state cross section is 4.6%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "M",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainties were obtained",
                " using the procedure specially described in text."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Photoneutron cross sections for 181Ta(g,n) 180Ta-m",
                " were determined from simultaneous measurements of",
                " total cross sections (SIG-tot) and ground-state cross",
                " sections (SIG-gs) for 180Ta in photodisintegration of",
                " 181Ta with laser Compton backscattering gamma-rays.",
                " Techniques of direct neutron counting and",
                " photoactivation were used for measurement of SIG-tot",
                " and SIG-gs, respectively. The partial cross sections",
                " for the isomeric state serves as a novel probe of",
                " nuclear level density of 180Ta. Implications for the",
                " p- and s- processes nucleosynthesis of 180Ta-m are",
                " given."
              ]
            }
          ],
